The want to improve yourself or others is the basis of greed.<br>
<br>
I'm sure when your guild tries something new.. The first thing that comes out of a few people's minds is  What does this thing drop?  not  How hard is it? or How fun will this be?<br>
<br>
That is greed talking for the first one but I don't see a problem with that because the person who asks is either limited by points or  by someone's choice or they just want the guy to drop some good loot for others which is still linked to greed.<br>
<br>
If a mob dropped no loot at all.. Would people still do him? Those who wouldn't are motivated by greed.. Not necessarily a bad thing... Depends on the situation.<br>
<br>
I do look outside my guild.. It doesn't matter what guild you are in.. Greed excessive or not is in everyone.. To the level 1 to the lvl65 with AA.  Its a basic human feeling that affects all.. It is an asset if you use it right.. It is a liability when you let it consume you.<br>
<br>
It may not affect you at all.. You maybe the Santa of Norrath never taking ahead of anyone else.. Only playing for the sheer thrill of playing.. There are definitely those out there and I tip my cap to them but the majority want loot, levels and to be the best they can be.  Nothing wrong with that.<br>
